---
title: "About — Slade Networks"
description: "Meet Andrew Slade — the person behind every Slade Networks install. Owner-operated UniFi networking for homes and businesses in the Finger Lakes, NY."
navActive: about
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .aboutGrid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.1fr .9fr;
      gap: 20px;
      align-items: start;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .aboutCard {
      background: var(--white);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      border-radius: var(--r-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
      padding: 28px;
    }

    .aboutCard h2 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      font-size: 20px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    .aboutCard p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-500);
      font-size: 14.5px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      max-width: 92ch;
    }
    .aboutCard p + p { margin-top: 12px; }

    .founderRow {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr;
      gap: 20px;
      align-items: start;
      margin-top: 14px;
    }

    .headshot {
      width: 140px;
      height: 140px;
      border-radius: var(--r-xl);
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      background: var(--gray-50);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }

    .headshot img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      display: block;
    }

    .founderMeta {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-500);
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .pillRow {
      margin-top: 16px;
      display: flex;
      gap: 10px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .pill {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      padding: 8px 14px;
      border-radius: var(--r-full);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      background: var(--gray-50);
      color: var(--gray-600);
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1;
      white-space: nowrap;
      transition: border-color .2s var(--ease), background .2s var(--ease);
    }
    .pill:hover {
      border-color: var(--primary-200);
      background: var(--primary-50);
      color: var(--primary);
    }

    .valuesGrid {
      margin-top: 18px;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 14px;
    }

    .ctaSection { padding: 0 0 72px }

    @media(max-width:980px) {
      .aboutGrid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }

    @media(max-width:700px) {
      .founderRow { grid-template-columns: 100px 1fr; }
      .headshot { width: 100px; height: 100px; border-radius: var(--r-lg); }
      .valuesGrid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          Owner-operated
        </div>
        <h1>The Person Behind the Work</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          Slade Networks is a one-person operation. Every consultation, installation, and support call is handled directly by Andrew — no subcontractors, no middlemen, and no system left behind without a proper walkthrough.
        </p>

        <div class="heroButtons">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Get a free consultation</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/services/">View services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="aboutGrid">

          <div class="aboutCard reveal">
            <h2>How we work</h2>
            <p>
              We design, install, and support network infrastructure for homes and small businesses across the Finger Lakes.
              Most projects use UniFi — a single platform for routing, switching, Wi-Fi, cameras, and VoIP — so everything runs through one dashboard and is straightforward to maintain.
            </p>
            <p>
              Whether it's a new build or a fix for poor coverage, unreliable cameras, or tangled wiring, the approach is the same:
              thorough planning, clean installation, proper RF design, and a system that's documented and easy to manage long after we leave.
            </p>

            <div class="valuesGrid reveal-stagger">
              <div class="infoCard">
                <h3>Built to last</h3>
                <p>Stable configurations, clean physical installs, and disciplined update practices so nothing breaks unexpectedly.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="infoCard">
                <h3>Easy to maintain</h3>
                <p>Clear labeling, organized cabling, and documentation so future changes and troubleshooting stay simple.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="infoCard">
                <h3>Secure by default</h3>
                <p>Network segmentation, proper access controls, and practical hardening — no unnecessary complexity.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="infoCard">
                <h3>Local and available</h3>
                <p>Based in Penn Yan, with responsive communication and flexible scheduling throughout every project.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="aboutCard reveal">
            <h2>Andrew Slade</h2>

            <div class="founderRow">
              <div class="headshot">
                <img src="/assets/Headshot.jpg" alt="Andrew Slade, founder of Slade Networks" loading="lazy">
              </div>

              <div>
                <p style="margin:0; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.01em; color:var(--gray-900);">Founder</p>
                <p class="founderMeta" style="margin-top:8px;">
                  Andrew started Slade Networks because he saw too many homes and businesses in the Finger Lakes stuck with unreliable networks and no one local to call.
                  He holds a Cisco CCNA certification and is completing his Computer Science degree at St. Bonaventure University.
                  His focus is practical, real-world networking — consistent performance, clean installs, and systems that work the same way on day 300 as they did on day one.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pillRow" aria-label="Credentials">
              <span class="pill">Computer Science &mdash; St. Bonaventure University</span>
              <span class="pill">Cisco CCNA</span>
              <span class="pill">UniFi deployments</span>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Want to work with us?</h2>
            <p>Tell us what you're dealing with and we'll respond with clear next steps — no sales pitch, just a plan.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Start a conversation</a>
            <a class="btn" href="mailto:info@sladenetworks.com">Email us directly</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
